The key insight is to recognize that a rotation matrix in 2D has the form:
$\begin{pmatrix} 
\cos \theta & -\sin \theta \\
\sin \theta & \cos \theta
\end{pmatrix}$

Where $\theta$ is the angle of rotation. By setting up an equation with the given input and output vectors, we can solve for $\cos \theta$ and $\sin \theta$. Once we have these values, we can apply the rotation matrix to the vector $\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$ to get the final rotated vector.
1) The rotation matrix must be of the form:
   $\begin{pmatrix}
   \cos \theta & -\sin \theta \\
   \sin \theta & \cos \theta
   \end{pmatrix}$

2) Set up the equation:
   $\begin{pmatrix}
   \cos \theta & -\sin \theta \\
   \sin \theta & \cos \theta
   \end{pmatrix}
   \begin{pmatrix}
   13 \\ 0
   \end{pmatrix} =
   \begin{pmatrix}
   5 \\ -12
   \end{pmatrix}$

3) This gives us:
   $\cos \theta = \frac{5}{13}$ and $\sin \theta = -\frac{12}{13}$

4) Apply the rotation matrix with the solved values to the vector $\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$:
   $\begin{pmatrix}
   \frac{5}{13} & \frac{12}{13} \\
   -\frac{12}{13} & \frac{5}{13}
   \end{pmatrix}
   \begin{pmatrix}
   0 \\ 1
   \end{pmatrix} =
   \begin{pmatrix}
   12/13 \\ 5/13
   \end{pmatrix}$

The key to solving this problem is to recognize that we can set up a proportion to find the number of Popsicles Megan can finish in a given time. By converting the given time (4 hours and 30 minutes) into minutes, we can easily compare it to the rate at which Megan consumes Popsicles (1 Popsicle every 15 minutes). This allows us to set up a proportion and solve for the number of Popsicles Megan can finish in the given time.
Let $p$ be the number of Popsicles Megan can finish in 4 hours and 30 minutes. If we convert that period of time into minutes, we find that 4 hours and 30 minutes is equal to $(4)(60)+30=270$ minutes. From here, we can set up the proportion  $$\begin{align*} \frac{x}{270}& =\frac{1}{15}
\\\Rightarrow \qquad x& =\left(\frac{1}{15}\right)(270)
\\\Rightarrow \qquad x& =\boxed{18}
\end{align*}$$
Megan can finish $\boxed{18}$ Popsicles in 4 hours and 30 minutes.
